# Self-signed dev certificate material — never commit.
#
# Both cert AND key are now gitignored. Earlier we tracked server.crt
# "because it's public", but that created an asymmetric tracking state:
# crt followed branches, key followed disk, branch switches reliably
# desynced them and crashed nginx with "key values mismatch". Better to
# treat the matched pair atomically: each dev / host regenerates locally,
# git stays out of it.
#
# Regenerate (matching pair, with SAN for browsers ≥ Chrome 58):
#
#   openssl req -x509 -nodes -days 3650 -newkey rsa:2048 \
#     -keyout server.key -out server.crt \
#     -subj "/C=TW/ST=Taiwan/L=Taipei/O=CSP Platform/CN=localhost" \
#     -addext "subjectAltName=DNS:localhost,DNS:<hostname>,IP:127.0.0.1,IP:<lan-ip>" \
#     -addext "keyUsage=digitalSignature,keyEncipherment" \
#     -addext "extendedKeyUsage=serverAuth"
#
# Verify match: diff <(openssl x509 -in server.crt -pubkey -noout) \
#                    <(openssl pkey -in server.key -pubout)
*.crt
*.crt.bak
*.key
*.key.bak
*.pem
